nested functions:
---------------------
====> A Function inside another Function.
      It is called nested nested function

====> syntax:
              def outerfunctionname(argumentslist):
                  def innerfunctionname-1(argumentslist):
                      body of the function
                  def innerfunctionname-2(argumentslist):
                      body of the function
                  def innerfunctionname-3(argumentslist):
                      body of the function
                  ---
                  ---
                  def innerfunctionname-n(argumentslist):
                      body of the function

ex-1:  write a program demo for nested functions, to display messages
def message():
    def mng():
        print('Good morning to all')                            
    def aft():
        print('Good afternoon to all')
    def evg():
        print('Good evening to all')                 
    def ngt():
        print('Good night to all')

    mng()
    aft()
    evg()
    ngt()
 
 

message()   




ex-2:  write a program demo for nested functions, to perform arithmetic operations  
method-1:  
def arithmeticoperations():
    def addition(x,y):
        print(x+y)                         
    def subtraction(x,y):
        print(x-y)
    def multiplication(x,y):
        print(x*y)                 
    def division(x,y):
        print(x/y)

    a = 11
    b = 2
    addition(a,b)
    subtraction(a,b)
    multiplication(a,b)
    division(a,b)
 
 

arithmeticoperations()   


method-2: 
def arithmeticoperations(x,y):
    def addition():
        print(x+y)                         
    def subtraction():
        print(x-y)
    def multiplication():
        print(x*y)                 
    def division():
        print(x/y)

     
    addition()
    subtraction()
    multiplication()
    division()
 
 
a = 11
b = 2
arithmeticoperations(a,b)   


 


